'''Shanghai Fukong Interactive Entertainment''' (chinese: <big>富控互动</big>), previously known as '''Zhongji Holding'''{{CiteGeneral|url=http://www.reuters.com/finance/stocks/600634.SS/key-developments/article/3541056|title=Shanghai Fukong Interactive Entertainment Co Ltd (600634.SS) Key Developments {{!}} Reuters.com|date=6 March 2017|accessdate=2017-04-05|publisher=Reuters|archiveurl=https://archive.fo/pAOze|archivedate=5 April 2017}}, is a venture capital firm that started in June 2016 and bought all investments from [[rsw:Insight Venture Partners|Insight Venture partners]], [[rsw:The Raine Group|The Raine Group]] and [[rsw:Spectrum Equity Investors|Spectrum Venture partners]] for a 100% stake in [[Jagex]] for $300,000,000 USD.{{CiteGeneral|url=
http://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2016-03-15-chinese-mining-company-buys-runescape-dev-for-usd300m-report |title=Chinese mining company buys Runescape dev for $300m - report |accessdate=2016-10-09 |author=Eurogamer}}{{CiteGeneral|url=http://venturebeat.com/2016/09/28/runescape-creator-jagex-is-now-part-of-a-new-chinese-games-company/ |title=RuneScape creator Jagex is now part of a new Chinese games company |accessdate=2016-10-09 |author=Venture Beat}}

It was formed by employees of [[rsw:Shandong Hongda|Shandong Hongda]] who originally put forward the intent to buyout all stakes in Jagex for $300,000,000 USD in April 2016.

Fukong Interactive Entertainment is a subsidiary of Shanghai Zhongji Enterprise Group which is traded publicly on the Chinese Stock Market under 600634.

